						Vigilant Capital Management LLC Acquires 9,559 Shares of Abbott Laboratories (ABT)					

						 June 28th, 2017  - 0 comments - Filed Under -
 by Mark Dietrich 


							Filed Under: Investing - SEC Filing Articles 






Tweet










Vigilant Capital Management LLC boosted its position in shares of  Abbott Laboratories (NYSE:ABT) by 4.9% during the first quarter, Holdings Channel reports. The institutional investor  owned 204,754 shares of the healthcare product maker’s stock after buying an additional 9,559 shares during the period. Abbott Laboratories comprises approximately  1.6% of Vigilant Capital Management LLC’s portfolio, making the stock its 25th largest position. Vigilant Capital Management LLC’s holdings in Abbott Laboratories were worth $9,093,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
Other large investors have also recently modified their holdings of the company. Norges Bank bought a new position in shares of  Abbott Laboratories during the fourth quarter worth about $598,897,000.  Westwood Holdings Group Inc. bought a new position in shares of  Abbott Laboratories during the fourth quarter worth about $168,455,000.  Dimensional Fund Advisors LP increased its position in shares of  Abbott Laboratories by 83.1% in the fourth quarter. Dimensional Fund Advisors LP now owns 6,794,786 shares of the healthcare product maker’s stock worth $260,987,000 after buying an additional 3,082,971 shares during the last quarter.  Asset Management One Co. Ltd. increased its position in shares of  Abbott Laboratories by 1,654.9% in the fourth quarter. Asset Management One Co. Ltd. now owns 2,643,491 shares of the healthcare product maker’s stock worth $101,518,000 after buying an additional 2,492,853 shares during the last quarter.  Finally, UBS Asset Management Americas Inc. increased its position in shares of  Abbott Laboratories by 57.1% in the fourth quarter. UBS Asset Management Americas Inc. now owns 6,525,001 shares of the healthcare product maker’s stock worth $250,625,000 after buying an additional 2,370,573 shares during the last quarter. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own  71.10% of the company’s stock. 
Abbott Laboratories (NYSE ABT) opened at 48.67 on Wednesday. The stock’s 50 day moving average price is $45.37 and its 200 day moving average price is $43.20. Abbott Laboratories has a 52 week low of $36.76 and a 52 week high of $49.30. The firm has a market capitalization of $84.46 billion, a P/E ratio of 50.65 and a beta of 1.08. 




Abbott Laboratories (NYSE:ABT) last posted its quarterly earnings results on Wednesday, April 19th. The healthcare product maker reported $0.48 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.43 by $0.05. Abbott Laboratories had a return on equity of 14.91% and a net margin of 6.74%. The firm had revenue of $6.34 billion for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $6.16 billion. During the same period in the previous year, the business earned $0.41 earnings per share. The company’s revenue for the quarter was up 29.7% compared to the same quarter last year.  On average, equities analysts expect that  Abbott Laboratories will post $2.47 EPS for the current year. 
The firm also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Tuesday, August 15th. Investors of record on Friday, July 14th will be paid a $0.265 dividend. The ex-dividend date is Wednesday, July 12th. This represents a $1.06 dividend on an annualized basis and a dividend yield of 2.18%. Abbott Laboratories’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is presently 110.42%. 
