Larry serves clients as a Wealth Advisor and is the firm’s Chief Compliance Officer.  Prior to joining Vigilant, Larry served as President and CEO and was a member of the Board of Directors of Acadia Trust, N.A., a subsidiary of Camden National Corporation.  As CEO, he had overall strategic and operational responsibility for the firm’s investment management, trust, retirement plan and advisory services.  He also directed the activities of the brokerage division of Camden National Bank.  During his tenure at Acadia Trust, Larry managed portfolios for high net worth individuals, non-profits and endowments, and retirement plan accounts.  Larry earned a B.S. in business administration from the University of Maine.  He completed the College for Financial Planning professional education program and is a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ practitioner.  Larry is a member of the University of Maine Business School Advisory Board, current member and past President of the Maine Estate Planning Council, former President of the Scarborough Boys Lacrosse Booster Club and previous 10-year board member of the YMCA of Southern Maine.  Larry resides in Scarborough, ME with his wife, Brenda, and their children.
 
